# ============================================================================
# Rule 12 - Enterprise Coding Standards
# ============================================================================

## Purpose

Every line of code must be

- Readable
- Maintainable
- Testable
- Observable
- Secure
- Consistent

Code should communicate business intent.

Never write clever code.

Write understandable code.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Coding Philosophy

Prefer

Simple

↓

Readable

↓

Maintainable

↓

Performant

Avoid

Complex

↓

Smart

↓

Magic

↓

Hidden Behavior

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Java Version

Always use

Java 21

Use modern Java features where appropriate

- Records
- Sealed Classes
- Pattern Matching
- Switch Expressions
- Text Blocks
- Virtual Threads (when approved)

Never use deprecated APIs.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# SOLID

Every implementation follows

S

Single Responsibility

O

Open Closed

L

Liskov

I

Interface Segregation

D

Dependency Inversion

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Clean Code

Methods

Small

Classes

Focused

Variables

Meaningful

Packages

Business Oriented

Never create God Classes.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Naming

Classes

LeadService

CustomerAggregate

WorkflowExecutor

Methods

qualifyLead()

assignAgent()

scheduleAppointment()

Variables

customerId

tenantId

leadScore

Never

temp

obj

data

test1

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Package Structure

Every service

domain

application

api

repository

events

mapper

integration

config

security

Never use package-by-layer across the repository.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Constructor Injection

Always

Constructor Injection

Never

Field Injection

Example

Good

private final LeadRepository repository;

Bad

@Autowired

private LeadRepository repository;

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Immutability

Prefer immutable objects.

Use

record

Value Objects

final fields

Avoid mutable shared state.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Records

Use Java Records for

DTO

Events

Commands

Queries

Responses

Do not use records for JPA entities.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Entities

Entity responsibilities

Business Rules

State Changes

Invariant Protection

Never expose setters for unrestricted mutation.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Services

Application Services

Coordinate

Domain Services

Contain domain behavior shared across aggregates

Never create utility services with unrelated responsibilities.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Interfaces

Create interfaces only when

Multiple implementations

External contracts

Testing boundary

Do not create interfaces "just in case."

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Exceptions

Use custom exceptions.

Examples

LeadNotFoundException

DuplicateLeadException

TenantAccessDeniedException

Never throw generic Exception.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Logging

Use

SLF4J

Structured Logging

Always log

CorrelationId

TenantId

Business Event

Never log

Passwords

Secrets

Tokens

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Null Handling

Never return null.

Use

Optional

Empty Collections

Meaningful Exceptions

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Collections

Return

List.of()

Collections.emptyList()

Immutable collections where possible.

Never return null collections.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Streams

Use Streams

For readable transformations.

Do not use Streams if loops are clearer.

Avoid deeply nested stream pipelines.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Constants

Use

private static final

Never hardcode

URLs

Roles

Permissions

Magic Numbers

Configuration

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Configuration

Use

application.properties

Environment Variables

Spring ConfigurationProperties

Never hardcode configuration values.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Validation

Always use

Bean Validation

@Valid

@NotNull

@NotBlank

Never manually validate simple request objects.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Transactions

@Transactional

Application Service only.

Never

Controller

Repository

Feign Client

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Mapping

Use

MapStruct

Preferred

Manual Mapper

If mapping is simple

Never map inside Controller.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# REST

Controllers

Only

Validate

Delegate

Return DTO

Never

Business Logic

Repository Calls

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Repository

One Repository

One Aggregate Root

Never create GenericRepository.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Events

Business State Change

↓

Domain Event

↓

Integration Event

↓

Outbox

Never publish Kafka directly from Controller.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Async

Use async for

Media Processing

Imports

AI

Workflow

Notifications

Avoid blocking long-running operations.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Multi-Tenancy

Every

Query

Cache Key

Event

Workflow

Must include

tenantId

Never bypass tenant validation.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Security

Never

Hardcode Secrets

Bypass Authorization

Skip Validation

Trust Client Input

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Performance

Avoid

N+1 Queries

SELECT *

Nested Remote Calls

Large Transactions

Repeated AI Calls

Repeated Embeddings

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Media

Store

Images

Videos

PDF

Audio

Reports

↓

S3

Never store binary data in PostgreSQL.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# AI

Never call

OpenAI

Gemini

Claude

Directly

Always use

AI Service

Provider Abstraction

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

